<HEADLINE>
Chile seeks women's soccer world cup organization in 2015.
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 2 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Chile announced Friday its will to bid to host the women's soccer
World Cup 2015.
</P>
<P>
Chilean President Michelle Bachelet made the announcement when
receiving the president of the Organizer Committee of the Women's
Soccer World Cup in Germany-2011, Steffi Jones.
</P>
<P>
Vice Minister of Sports Jaime Pizarro, other authorities of
soccer World Cup, like the chief of Women's Soccer Development of
FIFA Mayrilian Cruz-Blanco attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Bachelet thanked the international delegation visit and presented
the advances on the stadiums construction for the Women's World
Cup sub 20 that will take place this year in Chile.
</P>
<P>
"We have to prove not only that we can have a good organization
and good stadiums, but now we have to fill these buildings and
show the world that in 2008 we will have a big party". Said
Bachelet.
</P>
<P>
The international tournament would take place in different cities
in Chile between November 19 and December 7 this year and will
come together 16 countries like Germany, Brazil, China, France,
England and Japan.
</P>
